MBOMBELA &#8211; Home affairs closed their offices early this afternoon, telling those who want to enter only, &#8220;We are closed until further notice.&#8221;Lowvelder visited the offices at 11:00, whereby everything appeared to be business as usual. Upon revisiting an hour and a half later, some furniture and computer equipment had been taken out of the office, and people were shown away at the door.This happened after the sheriff allegedly confiscated the computers and furniture from the office, according to an anonymous tip.Management could not comment on the matter, but more information will be posted as it is made available.